ll for quite a while with very little downtime.  If the puller took a little extra time finding a mob, I would twist regen and mana song and the shaman would cannibalize, and we were good to go again.<br><br>Anyone else have any thoughts on Amp? <p><center><img src=http://www.rit.edu/~jjg1764/taborsig2.jpg ><BR>30th Tale Jharin of <a href="http://www.eternalsinn.net">Eternal Sinn</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uleolan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leolan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><FONT COLOR=AA0000><B>Lanys.com Administrator</B></FONT></span><br> <font color=#000033>(3/1/02 8:16:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumbard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=496.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.fallenlegacy.com/leolan/leopic.asp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thoughts on amplification?</span><hr size=1> Amp has limited usefulness, as it only effects sung songs, but does have its uses, especially pre-60 (since Puretone makes it wrap).  It shouldn't effect slowing rates though. <p> - Leo<br> <a href="mailto:leolan@fallenlegacy.com">leolan@fallenlegacy.com</a><p><small>"You must be willing to fail if you want to succeed."</small></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utaborcarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taborcarn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(3/1/02 8:31:24 am)</font><br>   <